# Environment Variables Reference

## LLM Provider Configuration

### Cloud Provider (OpenAI)
```env
# Required for cloud AI features
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-actual-key-here
```

Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys

### Local Provider (Ollama)
```env
# Enable offline local LLM (completely free, no internet needed)
LOCAL_LLM_ENABLED=true
LOCAL_LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
LOCAL_LLM_MODEL=mistral
LOCAL_LLM_TIMEOUT=300000
```

## Database Configuration
```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/shop_db
```

## Stripe Integration
```env
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_...
```

## Google Cloud Storage
```env
GCP_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
GCP_KEY_FILE=/path/to/service-account.json
```

## Twilio SMS
```env
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=AC...
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=...
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+1234567890
```

## Session Security
```env
SESSION_SECRET=your-random-session-secret-here
```

## Licensing
```env
MASTER_LICENSE_KEY=RSS-MASTER-REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-SECRET
```

## Email (Outreach / Campaigns)
```env
# Gmail quick setup (recommended for desktop)
GMAIL_SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
GMAIL_SMTP_APP_PASSWORD=your-16-char-app-password
# Optional generic SMTP override
# OUTREACH_SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# OUTREACH_SMTP_PORT=465
# OUTREACH_SMTP_SECURE=true
# OUTREACH_SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# OUTREACH_SMTP_PASS=your-16-char-app-password

# Sender shown to recipients (must match provider policy)
OUTREACH_FROM_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com
```

## Application Settings
```env
NODE_ENV=development|production
PORT=3000
LOG_LEVEL=info|debug|error
CORS_ORIGIN=*|http://localhost:3000
```

## Example .env file (offline setup)
```env
# Local AI - Completely offline and free
LOCAL_LLM_ENABLED=true
LOCAL_LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
LOCAL_LLM_MODEL=mistral
LOCAL_LLM_TIMEOUT=300000

# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/shop_db

# Session
SESSION_SECRET=your-secret-key-change-this-in-production

# Application
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
```

## Getting Started

1. Copy this template to `.env` in the `api-server` directory
2. Fill in the required values
3. Run `npm run dev`
